criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion:

          -  patients with ischemic stroke or non-traumatic intracerebral hemorrhage, with residual
             deficit origin;

          -  age 45 or older

          -  stroke severity (3-8 on the NIH stroke severity scale); and

          -  able to participate in the intervention (due to, for example, ability to communicate
             or level of social connectedness).

        Exclusion:

          -  patients living outside the greater Boston area;

          -  admitted from a nursing home;

          -  terminally ill;

          -  severely aphasic;

          -  significantly cognitively impaired;

          -  unable to speak English; and

          -  under 45 years of age.
